727465f-b.title: Queens: Newton Road - 47th Street
727465f-b.text:
Newtown Road, west from the S.E. corner of 47th Street, showing
in their order, prominently Nos. 47-08, 46-16, 46-02, and 45-18.
These houses are a few that remain in the Middleton settlement,
started about 1800. This settlement was located on Newtown Ave.,
between Grand Ave. and Broadway.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727466f-a.title: Queens: Newton Road - 47th Street
727466f-a.text:
47-01 Newtown Road, at the N.E. corner of 47th Street,
showing an old house, typical of late nineteenth century
construction. lIn rear of it, on 48th Street, is an old farm-
house. Later views show also the rear of the new William
Cullen Bryant High School. 47th Street is in the foreground.
The house was owned by J. Murphy in 1873.
P. L. Sperr  View 1r October 31, 1936
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 2,3I September 5, 1940
